SVA - SV3 and SV4, normed

Kamil Łopuszański

12/16/2019

Normalize the data

geneexp.complete.norm <- t(scale(t(geneexp.complete), center = TRUE, scale = TRUE))

Box plot the normalized to check

boxplot(geneexp.complete.norm)

SVA - cell.line

mod = model.matrix(~as.factor(cell.line), data=pheno)
mod0 = model.matrix(~1, data=pheno)
sva_output = sva(as.matrix(geneexp.complete.norm), mod, mod0, n.sv=4)
## Number of significant surrogate variables is:  4 
## Iteration (out of 5 ):1  2  3  4  5
sva_cell.line <- tibble(SV3=sva_output$sv[,3],
                        SV4=sva_output$sv[,4],
                        cell.line=as.factor(pheno$cell.line), 
                        tissue=as.factor(pheno$tissue),
                        disease.state=as.factor(pheno$disease.state))

ggplot(sva_cell.line) + geom_point(aes(x=SV3, y=SV4, col=cell.line)) + 
  theme(aspect.ratio = 0.4, legend.position = "top")

ggplot(sva_cell.line) + geom_point(aes(x=SV3, y=SV4, col=tissue))

ggplot(sva_cell.line) + geom_point(aes(x=SV3, y=SV4, col=disease.state)) +          
  theme(legend.position = "top", aspect.ratio = 0.4) + guides(col = guide_legend(nrow = 13))

sva_cell.line <- tibble(SV3 = sva_output$sv[,3], SV4 = sva_output$sv[,4], cell.line = as.factor(pheno$cell.line))
sva_cell.line <- gather(sva_cell.line,"sv","value",-cell.line)

ggplot(sva_cell.line) + geom_violin(aes(x=cell.line,y=value)) +
  geom_jitter(aes(x=cell.line,y=value,col=cell.line)) + facet_wrap(~ sv, ncol = 1) +
  theme(legend.position = "top")
